can we please add another test where we have a failed query in the cache? This used to bite us when the implementation was still `ensureQueryData` - the query was there, but data was not.

I think you can get that with:


```
await queryClient.prefetchQuery({
  ...queryOpts,
  queryFn: () => { 
    throw new Error("oops")
  },
  retry: false
})
```

prefetching doesn't throw so there shouldn't be any try/catch needed.

